      • convert

        public java.util.List<ReferencedClass> convert(java.lang.String body)
                                        throws java.io.IOException
        Coverts a CSV-String to a List of Objects(class ReferencedClass). A row of the CSV-String is a Referenced Class Object. This is done by Iterating over the Annotations (SerializedName) and comparing them to the header of the CSV (first line) and the DataSet's Postition (in order to map it to the header).
        Parameters:
        body - CSV-String to be converted
        Returns:
        List of ReferencedClass-Object (containing the rows of the CSV as Java-Objects)
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException
